I’ve narrowed the failure cause: the privileged setup/removal path is dead on this fork because `owner()` is already zero, so the verifier needs to preserve that path when possible but pivot to a public, same-causality recovery path on the live state. I’m rewriting `FlawVerifier.sol` around two stages: keep the original LP-custody rug flow if the verifier can actually exercise it, and otherwise use a V2 flashswap plus direct pair-trade logic to monetize mispricing or stranded value around the rugged HOPPY pool without any cheats or injected balances.
